We recommend the Local Chief Executive to:
Conduct public bidding on the procurement of goods and services which exceeded the threshold prescribed in Annex “H” of the 2016 Revised IRR;
Require the end-user units to prepare PPMPs for various programs, projects and activities of the agency which shall include vital information mentioned in Section 7.3.2 of the procurement law and the BAC Secretariat to consolidate same into an APP.
Require the BAC Secretariat to review carefully the contents of PPMPs and APP and ensure that all procurement of the agency is in accordance with the approved PPMPs and APP;
Implement strictly timelines on the posting and submission of procurement reports;
Establish procurement timelines in consonance with project schedules, including a cut-off date for processing requisitions and issuance of purchase orders to ensure receipt of most of the procured items in time for the project implementation;
Strict observance of RA 9184 and its IRR, and other existing rules and regulations on government procurement is enjoined as well as imposition of control measures to ensure that procurement is effected in an efficient, economical and effective manner that is most advantageous to the government and to prevent possible disallowances for such violation.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive to:
Identify authorized Local projects that necessitate the hiring of job order workers;
Align the hiring of job order personnel services with the Sanggunian authorized local projects.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive to: 

a.)Direct the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer, and Municipal Budget Officer to promptly submit the required reports and transaction documents as prescribed in various rules and regulations mentioned herein;

b) Direct the Municipal Accountant to cause the submission of the unsubmitted financial reports and disbursement vouchers with corresponding supporting documents;

We recommend that the local chief executive to: 

Secure copies of PNDF Volume 1, current edition, and to direct the Municipal Health Officer and other requisitioning officers to refer as basis for procurements of drugs the PNDF and thereby, require attachment of certification for each request the purchase thereof to ensure conformity with PNDF;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to properly ascertain the propriety of accounts used in the accounting entries made in the procurement of drugs and medicines.
